On mobile, the game header should read as a horizontally scrollable tab strip instead of a padded row of buttons. This change makes the header span the full viewport while keeping the active page centered and leaving a small preview of neighboring buttons visible.

- **Mobile header layout**
  - Extend the header container to the viewport edges on small screens.
  - Keep horizontal snap scrolling, but reduce the inter-button gap so adjacent tabs peek in and signal more content off-screen.
  - Preserve the existing one-button-at-a-time focus for the active route.

- **Coverage for the layout contract**
  - Update the colocated header CSS test to assert the full-width mobile container behavior in addition to the existing snap-scrolling rules.

- **Relevant CSS**
  ```css
  @media(max-width: 768px) {
    .header {
      gap: var(--space-md);
      overflow-x: auto;
      padding-inline: var(--space-md);
      position: relative;
      right: var(--space-xl);
      scroll-snap-type: x mandatory;
      width: calc(100% + var(--space-xl) * 2);
    }
  }
  ```

